            <p><a href="http://www.latimes.com/business/technology/la-fi-tn-facebook-workplace-20161010-snap-story.html" target="_blank">Facebook Launches Workplace, a Business Version of Facebook</a></p>
            <p>Facebook has created a separate version of its popular social network. Called Workplace, this communication tool was recently launched for businesses, nonprofits, and other organizations. The platform is not linked to users’ existing Facebook accounts, making it entirely autonomous in that sense, and is ad-free. Fees are based on how many employees an organization has that would be using the platform. Workplace is free for nonprofits and educational institutions, and aims to connect the professional sector of the Internet using features such as group chats, video calls, individual worker profiles, and newsfeeds.</p>
