            <p><a href="http://searchengineland.com/google-patent-using-social-signals-impact-rankings-259656" target="_blank">Exploring a Newly-Granted Google Patent Around Social Signals</a></p>
            <p>A recently published patent offers clues about how Google views social signals and search results. The patent includes details about how each online searcher has a social graph linked to them, one that is created via their social media connections on sites, blogs, in email, and chat, etc. When Google is able to connect a user between these various web properties, a fuller picture of their social graph and connections is made. Likes and recommendations by the people to whom they are connected socially could ultimately be used to impact their search ranking, as this patent seems to suggest that social interactions may now be used as a factor in search ranking signals.</p>
