            <p>Recently, Facebook updated its recommendations, local events, and call-to-action buttons on pages for businesses. Recommendations can now be turned on for status updates where individual users are seeking advice. The events bookmark will also be updated in the coming weeks to allow users to browse recommendations for events by their popularity with friends. Lastly, Facebook has updated its calls to action for local business pages, allowing users the increased flexibility to request appointments, obtain a quote for services, order food from restaurants, and purchase tickets to events directly from a business’ page.</p>
